Ingredients.1: 2.0 cups shredded Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese blend

Ingredients.2: 1 cup butter, cut into small pieces

Ingredients.4: 1 teaspoon smoked paprika, or more to taste (Optional)

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).

Directions.2: Put Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese in a bowl; add butter. Cover bowl and let sit until warmed to room temperature.

Directions.3: Combine flour and paprika together in a separate bowl.

Directions.4: Mix cheese and butter together using your hands. Slowly add flour mixture to cheese-butter mixture until dough holds together in a ball. Roll dough onto a work surface, about 1/8-inch thick. Cut dough into cracker shapes using cookie cutters or a knife; sprinkle salt over dough. Arrange dough pieces on a baking sheet.

Directions.5: Bake in the preheated oven until crackers are crisp, 15 to 18 minutes.
